{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Momardi","author":"Tuesday Gutierrez"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"14e552c2-9cc5-5f5c-9f03-dae07957d7fa","excerpt":"My friend Cristina, Pach,  and I had a chance to attend a   sake-tasting event at the Japanese embassy  last Thursday and had fun drinking…","html":"<p>My friend Cristina, Pach,  and I had a chance to attend a <a href=\"http://www.japansociety.org.uk/14016/iwc-award-winning-sake-tasting-at-the-japanese-embassy/\"> sake-tasting event at the Japanese embassy</a> last Thursday and had fun drinking 14 of the award-winning sake (from the<a href=\"http://www.internationalwinechallenge.com/\"> International Wine Challenge</a>).  Despite our sake-newbieness, our favourite turned out to be the<a href=\"http://www.internationalwinechallenge.com/wine/150513/2011/Nabeshima-Daiginjo.aspx\" title=\"IWC Sake Winner\"> IWC Trophy Champion for 2011</a><strong>(Nabeshima Daiginjo, 2010). **The judges of the International Wine Challenge describe it as **“Soft with a sweet, fruity aroma. On the palate the flavours are dry, earthy and nutty with hints of fresh stone fruits. The finish is long with warming alcohol and lift.”</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Our palate needed some re-education on everything about sake</strong>. I’ve always thought sake should be served warm but we learned a special tidbit from a Japanese girl who told us that warm sake is a sign of low quality. </p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/sake1__gdnnng.jpg\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 427px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 149.88290398126463%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"sake1  gdnnng\"\n        title=\"sake1_\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/bc93183ef5b68f5b1704c2d0ab4bd46f/b2d50/sake1__gdnnng.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/bc93183ef5b68f5b1704c2d0ab4bd46f/2eca7/sake1__gdnnng.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/bc93183ef5b68f5b1704c2d0ab4bd46f/31141/sake1__gdnnng.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/bc93183ef5b68f5b1704c2d0ab4bd46f/b2d50/sake1__gdnnng.jpg 427w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 427px) 100vw, 427px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">sake1_</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      <strong>****</strong></a><span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>Sake-tasting event at the Japanese embassy. *© Photo by *<a href=\"http://eatpumpkin-pim.blogspot.com/\" title=\"Natsukipim\">Natsuki Pimienta Kikuya</a></em></span></p>\n<p>For a more professional sake advise, our blogger friend slash sake sommellier <strong><a href=\"http://natsukipim.com\" title=\"Natsukipim\">Natsuki Pimienta Kikuya</a></strong> wrote a more in-depth post at her blog. She is organising a sake charity event to support the Japan earthquake victims on <strong>Sept 20 at the Japanese embassy</strong>.  <strong>RSVP to kanpailondon@gmail.com</strong>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/kanpai_sake_yns0vb.jpg\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 400px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 88.75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"kanpai sake yns0vb\"\n        title=\"kanpai_sake\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/615a3225a3c0050d75fb869f45a510a6/10d2e/kanpai_sake_yns0vb.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/615a3225a3c0050d75fb869f45a510a6/9a025/kanpai_sake_yns0vb.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/615a3225a3c0050d75fb869f45a510a6/4eec6/kanpai_sake_yns0vb.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/615a3225a3c0050d75fb869f45a510a6/10d2e/kanpai_sake_yns0vb.jpg 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">kanpai_sake</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </a></p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/Nabeshima_Daiginjo_hkc2hd.jpg\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.71875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Nabeshima Daiginjo hkc2hd\"\n        title=\"Nabeshima_Daiginjo\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/9925006145060bc3cd53a840cf895381/8c020/Nabeshima_Daiginjo_hkc2hd.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/9925006145060bc3cd53a840cf895381/da4c4/Nabeshima_Daiginjo_hkc2hd.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/9925006145060bc3cd53a840cf895381/37caf/Nabeshima_Daiginjo_hkc2hd.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/9925006145060bc3cd53a840cf895381/8c020/Nabeshima_Daiginjo_hkc2hd.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/9925006145060bc3cd53a840cf895381/ec4bb/Nabeshima_Daiginjo_hkc2hd.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Nabeshima_Daiginjo</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </a><span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em><a href=\"http://nabeshima-saga.com/\"><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Fukuchiyo Shuzo</span></a> table Mr. Iimori, champion Sake producer this year</em></span><br>\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\">* with his “<strong>Nabeshima Daiginjo, 2010</strong>“. © Photo by <a href=\"http://eatpumpkin-pim.blogspot.com/\" title=\"Natsukipim\"><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Natsuki Pimienta Kikuya</span></a>*</span></p>\n<p>Beyond the sushi and the sake wooziness, I stumbled upon a brochure from the Da<strong>iwa Foundation announcing its Foundation Art Prize which is open to all British artists who previously haven’t had any solo exhibition in Japan.</strong> The winning artist will receive a participation fee of 5000 pounds, travel and accommodation costs for a 7 day period in Japan  plus assistance with introductions with key individuals in Japanese contemporary art. Open to all artists working in any medium. For more information check the Daiwa Foundation <a href=\"http://www.dajf.org.uk/grants-awards-prizes/daiwa-foundation-art-prize\" title=\"Daiwa Foundation website\">website</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/Image463_dhnuqx.png\">\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 357px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 54.34173669467788%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Image463 dhnuqx\"\n        title=\"Image463\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/2d38fc96e15ceac95e3c5cacc61c836b/53486/Image463_dhnuqx.png\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/2d38fc96e15ceac95e3c5cacc61c836b/c688f/Image463_dhnuqx.png 158w,\n/momardi/static/2d38fc96e15ceac95e3c5cacc61c836b/44241/Image463_dhnuqx.png 315w,\n/momardi/static/2d38fc96e15ceac95e3c5cacc61c836b/53486/Image463_dhnuqx.png 357w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 357px) 100vw, 357px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Image463</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </a></p>\n<p>Related Links:<br>\n<a href=\"http://http://mdn.mainichi.jp/mdnnews/national/news/20110908p2g00m0dm033000c.html\" title=\"Nabeshima\">Saga’s Nabeshima chosen as champion sake at London wine competition</a><br>\n<a href=\"http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/nb20110909a3.html\" title=\"Nabeshima wins\">Saga tipple named champion sake at London blind wine-tasting event</a> <a href=\"http://www.hospitalityandcateringnews.com/2011/09/supermarkets-reign-supreme-in-the-iwcs-world-of-wine/\" title=\"Supermarkets reign supreme\"><br>\nSupermarkets Reign Supreme in the IWC’s World of Wine</a> <a href=\"http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/nb20110909a3.html\" title=\"Nabeshima wins\"><br>\n</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Turning Japanese: Sake-Tasting Event and The Daiwa Foundation Art Prize 2011","date":"September 11, 2011"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2011-09-12---turning-japanese-sake-tasting-event-and-the-daiwa-foundation-art-prize-2011/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011-09-07---israeli-art-takes-centre-stage-in-freedom-of-expression-true-colours/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Israeli Art Takes Centre Stage in Freedom of Expression: True Colours"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011-09-15---last-twodays-mirror-of-judgement-michelangelo-pistoletto-at-the-serpentine-gallery/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Last Two Days of Mirror of Judgement: Michelangelo Pistoletto at the Serpentine Gallery"}}}}